  <front>
    <title>A Bandwidth Attribute for TURN</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-thomson-tram-turn-bandwidth-00"/>
    <author initials="M." surname="Thomson" fullname="Martin Thomson"/>
    <author initials="B." surname="Aboba" fullname="Dr. Bernard D. Aboba"/>
    <author initials="A." surname="Johnston" fullname="Alan Johnston"/>
    <author initials="O." surname="Moskalenko" fullname="Oleg Moskalenko"/>
    <date day="13" month="February" year="2014"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   An attribute is defined for Session Traversal Utilities for NAT
   (STUN) that allows for declarations of bandwidth limits on the
   negotiated flow.  The application of this attribute is the
   negotiation of bandwidth between a Traversal Using Relays around NAT
   (TURN) client and a TURN server.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
